				<td colspan="2"><span>While SOE has done some things that infuriate me, for the most part they have done a very good job at keeping the game &quot;new&quot; - I was going to say fresh but it is more or less the same things in new places.  Occasionally after these changes things get out of balance and they try to correct them usually (well always) this involves a nerf or two.  However, overall we are better off than we were before the expansions or addition of new items and content.
<br />

<br />
Take LDoN for example, before LDoN I was never the puller because no one would do a dungeon crawl.  It was always get to a spot and camp the h*ll out of it.  Now after they changed the way lull works but honestly lull was not used that much before ldon so it wasnt overpowered - which would you rather have LDoN or a 2 min lull?
<br />

<br />
And as far as new levels go - leveling from 1-10 was never very much fun after the first time.  10-20 wasnt much better so why not make leveling quicker to get to the part of the game where most players are?  
<br />

<br />
My one complaint now is that there is so much unused content out there.  Just try to get in to Paw or Seb (heck even Karnors is empty now)without brining your own group.  This makes it very hard to learn a zone.
<br />

<br />
It would be interesting to see an LDoN type change to these zones - but it would never happen.
<br />
</span></td>
