				<td colspan="2"><span>Yeah, one of my biggest complaints would be the unused content.  It seems like such a waste of gaming space when everyone just goes to the same zones to do stuff.  I would love to see more revamps, but not just making more uber mobs who drop uber loot.  I'd love to see more quests implemented.  Again, it doesn't have to be uber, just interesting and at least marginally worth doing.  If its neat, they will come.
<br />
I guess sometimes I too long for the days of yore...
<br />
The inherent problem I see is that the loot distribution is so unbalanced.  All the best stuff drops in the same places, and usually those same places have the best xp.  Even just a simple xp distribution, such as zone-wide xp modifiers (ala Paludal) could make for more zone usage.
<br />
Just my thoughts.
<br />
Longing for the good ole days,
<br />
Myrmion
